The paper deals with the relationship between flow-cut gaps and face covers in planar graphs, which involves topics such as graph theory, combinatorics, and optimization. Therefore, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are likely categories. The paper also involves analyzing the performance of algorithms, which falls under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and the use of stochastic embeddings, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
